[{"category":"section","location":"#VisGraphs","page":"Home","text":"Documentation for VisGraphs.\n\n","title":"VisGraphs"},{"category":"function","location":"#VisGraphs.generate_noisy_sine","page":"Home","text":"generate_noisy_sine(n::Int=100, noise::Float64=0.2)\n\nGenerate a noisy sine wave time series.\n\nThe signal is a sine wave over [0, 4π] with added Gaussian noise.\n\nReturns:     Vector{Float64}: noisy sine wave.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"VisGraphs.generate_noisy_sine"},{"category":"function","location":"#VisGraphs.generate_random","page":"Home","text":"generate_random(n::Int=100)\n\nGenerate a random time series.\n\nReturns:     Vector{Float64}: uniformly distributed random values in [0, 1).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"VisGraphs.generate_random"},{"category":"function","location":"#VisGraphs.generate_sine","page":"Home","text":"generate_sine(n::Int=100)\n\nGenerate a sine wave time series.\n\nReturns:     Vector{Float64}: sine wave sampled over [0, 4π].\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"VisGraphs.generate_sine"},{"category":"method","location":"#VisGraphs.hvg-Tuple{AbstractVector{<:Real}}","page":"Home","text":"hvg(x)\n\nConstruct a Horizontal Visibility Graph (HVG) from a time series x.\n\nArguments:     x::AbstractVector{<:Real}: time series containing finite numeric values.\n\nReturns:     Vector{Tuple{Int, Int}}: edges of the HVG.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"VisGraphs.hvg"},{"category":"method","location":"#VisGraphs.nvg-Tuple{AbstractVector{<:Real}}","page":"Home","text":"nvg(x)\n\nConstruct a Natural Visibility Graph (NVG) from a time series x.\n\nArguments:     x::AbstractVector{<:Real}: time series containing finite numeric values.\n\nReturns:     Vector{Tuple{Int, Int}}: edges of the NVG.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"VisGraphs.nvg"},{"category":"method","location":"#VisGraphs.plot_hvg-Tuple{AbstractVector{<:Real}}","page":"Home","text":"plot_hvg(x)\n\nCompute and visualize the Horizontal Visibility Graph (HVG) of a time series x.\n\nThe time series is plotted, and HVG edges are drawn as lines between visible points.\n\nArguments:     x::AbstractVector{<:Real}: finite-valued time series.\n\nReturns:     Plots.Plot: time series with HVG edges overlaid.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"VisGraphs.plot_hvg"},{"category":"method","location":"#VisGraphs.plot_nvg-Tuple{AbstractVector{<:Real}}","page":"Home","text":"plot_nvg(x)\n\nCompute and visualize the Natural Visibility Graph (NVG) of a time series x.\n\nThe time series is plotted, and NVG edges are drawn as lines between visible points.\n\nArguments:     x::AbstractVector{<:Real}: finite-valued time series.\n\nReturns:     Plots.Plot: time series with NVG edges overlaid.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"VisGraphs.plot_nvg"}]
